commit.message: ipc-rules: report min/max size for toplevels

simple-tile: do not tile views with min==max size

Fixes #2243
toplevel-interface: add min/max size APIs

Session lock plugin fixes (#2304)

* session-lock: minor state machine fixes.

- Ensure that if an output is added after the client crashes,
  the lock_crashed_node is displayed on that output.
  Currently that output would simply be unlocked, oops!
  - Create the lock_crashed_node as soon as the output state is
    created, instead of when the output is locked.
  - When a lock is destroyed, only disconnect the protocol signals,
    but leave output add/remove signals connected.

- If a client crashes and the lock enters ZOMBIE state, destroy
  it as soon as the next client locks, instead of waiting until
  it unlocks. This ensures there is only one lock_crashed_node
  per output at any given time.

* session-lock: support resizing outputs when locked

This is not perfect, because if the output is enlarged some of
the screen is visible for a bit until the client updates its
surface, but it works well enough for now.

* Fix formatting

Session lock plugin fixes (#2304)

* session-lock: minor state machine fixes.

- Ensure that if an output is added after the client crashes,
  the lock_crashed_node is displayed on that output.
  Currently that output would simply be unlocked, oops!
  - Create the lock_crashed_node as soon as the output state is
    created, instead of when the output is locked.
  - When a lock is destroyed, only disconnect the protocol signals,
    but leave output add/remove signals connected.

- If a client crashes and the lock enters ZOMBIE state, destroy
  it as soon as the next client locks, instead of waiting until
  it unlocks. This ensures there is only one lock_crashed_node
  per output at any given time.

* session-lock: support resizing outputs when locked

This is not perfect, because if the output is enlarged some of
the screen is visible for a bit until the client updates its
surface, but it works well enough for now.

* Fix formatting

commit.message: vswitch: do not allow workspace change from ipc without full capabilities

seat: avoid sending duplicate fake leave events when switching focus

Fixes #2291, Fixes #1635

simple-tile: refactor controller activation

More work for #2291

scale: do not let last_select_view become dangling

Otherwise, we may attempt to drag an unmapped or destroyed view, which
causes all sorts of issues down the chain.

Fixes #2286
Fixes #2289
Fixes #2292
Fixes #2293

move-drag-interface: remove output effect hook when drag ends

Fixes #2296

input-grab: do not grab input if activated for a non-focused output

Plugins grab input per-output, if grabbing for the non-focused output,
they shouldn't steal focus from the other output.

Fixes #2291

meson.build: manually check for glm header as a fallback

The CI sometimes misses the glm .pkgconfig/.cmake files, this has
happened in the past too. Just add a check for it.

grid: gracefully ignore views with no output

The IPC can toggle views like that and we cannot do anything about them.

Fixes #2284

xwayland: fix should_be_decorated() for inert views

Fixes #2298

vswitch: do not start moving views from ipc which are not mapped

Maybe fixes #2282 ?

tile: do not allow tiling pending-unmapped views

Otherwise, we might not get the view-unmapped signal for them, and we
would then not remove them from the tiling layout.

Fixes #2279

scale: do not read new focus in unmap handler

At that point, refocusing still hasn't happened, so simply reset the
view instead.

Fixes #2273

plugins: add xkb-bindings example

Fixes #1601
bindings-repository: add support for extension bindings

meson.build: add json as wayfire dependency (#2259)

* meson.build: add json as wayfire dependency

Do not use the subproject, because it will not get installed.

Json used to be optional before but nowadays so many plugins use IPC
that it doesn't make sense to have it as an optional feature.

* fixup! meson.build: add json as wayfire dependency
